  section
    section
      h3 Point selection problem
      figure.fragment.centering
        #d1(data-height='420')
      p.fragment.centering
        | How to define &quot;median&quot; for point set on plane?
      .dummy.fragment(data-toggle='diagram' data-target='#d1')
      p.fragment.centering
        | Is there always a point in many triangles?
    section
      h3 The planar case
      p Given $n$ points on the plane in general position.
      .fragment.panel
        .panel-header Boros&ndash;F&uuml;redi Theorem
        .panel-body
          p
            | There exists a point in $\ge$
            span.fragment.highlight-red $\frac{2}{9}$
            | ${n\choose 3}-O(n^2)$ triangles.
      br
      .fragment.panel
        .panel-header Bukh&ndash;Matou&scaron;ek&ndash;Nivasch Theorem
        .panel-body
          p The constant $\frac{2}{9}$ is the best possible by stretched grid!
    section
      h3 Higher dimensional case
      p Given $n$ points in $\mathbb{R}^d$ in general position.
      p.fragment A simplex is the convex hull of $d+1$ points.
      .fragment.panel
        .panel-header B&aacute;r&aacute;ny&apos;s Theorem
        .panel-body
          p There exists a point in $\ge c_d{n \choose d+1}$ simplices.
      p
      .panel.fragment
        .panel-header Bukh&ndash;Matou&scaron;ek&ndash;Nivasch Theorem
        .panel-body
          p We cannot hope for $c_d &gt; \frac{(d+1)!}{(d+1)^d}$ by stretched grid.
    section
      h3 Timeline
      .centering
        p
          img.round-200(src='img/barany.png')
          img.round-200.fragment(src='img/wagner.png' data-fragment-index='2')
          img.round-200.fragment(src='img/gromov.png' data-fragment-index='3')
        p
          | B&aacute;r&aacute;ny: a point is in $\ge$ 
          span.fragment.highlight-red(data-fragment-index='0') $c_d$
          | $n\choose d+1$ simplices.
      table.simple
        tr.fragment(data-fragment-index='1')
          td 1982
          td B&aacute;r&aacute;ny
          td $\frac{1}{(d+1)^d}$
          td
        tr.fragment(data-fragment-index='2')
          td 2003
          td Wagner
          td $\frac{(d^2+1)}{(d+1)^{d+1}}$
          td
        tr.fragment(data-fragment-index='3')
          td 2010
          td Gromov
          td
            | $\frac{2d}{(d+1)(d+1)!}$ 
            span.fragment(data-fragment-index='4') $&lt; \frac{(d+1)!}{(d+1)^d}$
          td
