  section
    section
      h3 Karasev&apos;s proof
      p
        | Given 3 (continuous) probability measures 
        span.red-text $m_0$
        | , 
        span.green-text $m_1$
        |  and 
        span.blue-text $m_2$
        | .
      .fragment
        p Proof by contradiction. Assume for every point $v$,
        p.centering
          | $\operatorname{Pr}\big(v \text{ is in} $ 
          span.colorful-triangle
          |  $ \big) &lt; p := 2/9.$
      .fragment
        p Plane (plus a point at infinity) and sphere are the same.
        #d3_4.centering
          span#d3.inline-diagram
            span#d3_1 $\infty$
          span.inline-text $\equiv$
          span#d4.inline-diagram
            span#d4_1 $\infty$
    section
      h3 Preparation
      ul
        li.fragment(data-fragment-index='1') Choose a sufficiently fine triangulation of sphere.
        li.fragment(data-fragment-index='3') Add &quot;buttress&quot; inside the sphere.
      .centering.div-with-margin
        figure#d5.fragment(data-fragment-index='2' data-height='380')
        figure#d6.fragment(data-fragment-index='4' data-height='380')
    section
      h3 Auxiliary map
      div
        p
          span.fragment.highlight-red(data-fragment-index='2') Gradually
          |  build a map from &quot;sphere with buttress&quot; to sphere:
        .div-with-margin.centering
          figure#d7(data-height='260')
          span#d7-5 $\overset{f}{\longrightarrow}$
          figure#d8(data-height='260')
        .fragment(data-fragment-index='1')
          p such that:
          ol
            li it is identity when restricted to the sphere;
            li
              | it is 
              span.fragment.highlight-red(data-fragment-index='2') economical
              | : e.g., image of each &quot;spike&quot; is small.
    section
      h3 Build economical map gradually
      p.fragment Step 1: Vertex $O$ (sphere center) $\mapsto \infty$ (the north pole).
      p.fragment Step 2: Want $\overline{PO}\mapsto \overline{P\infty}$; need to find line segment $\overline{P\infty}$.
      .panel.div-with-margin.fragment
        table.simple.left-aligned
          tbody
            tr
              td.panel-label Claim
              td
                | $\operatorname{Pr}\big(\overline{P\infty} \text{ intersects }$ 
                span.green-to-blue
                |  $\big)$ $&lt; p$ for some $\overline{P\infty}$.
      .panel.div-with-margin.fragment
        table.simple.left-aligned
          tbody
            tr
              td#td-5-3-obs.panel-label Obs
              td
                span.white-dot
                |  is in 
                span.colorful-triangle
                |  $\Longleftrightarrow$ 
                span.red-gray-ray
                |  intersects 
                span.green-to-blue
                | .
      p.fragment.centering
        | $\operatorname{Pr}\big($ 
        span.red-gray-ray
        |  intersects 
        span.green-to-blue
        |  $\big)=\operatorname{Pr}\big($
        span.white-dot
        |  is in 
        span.colorful-triangle
        |  $\big) &lt; p$
      p.fragment.centering
        | $\implies \operatorname{Pr}\big($
        span.red-gray-ray
        |  intersects 
        span.green-to-blue
        | $\;\big\vert\; $
        span.red-dot
        | $\big) &lt; p$ for some 
        span.red-dot
